-- China May Levy Property Tax That's 0.6% of Value, Securities Times Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-27T22:40:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/china-may-levy-property-tax-that-s-0-6-of-value-securities-times-reports.html
China may levy a property tax of
about 0.6 percent of the value of homes, the Securities Times
reported today, citing a person familiar with the situation.  First homes will be excluded from the tax, the Shenzhen-
based newspaper reported. Work on starting trials of the
property tax may start as early as the end of this year,
according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  